<br>
Of all the melee and hybrid epics, the only one that has shown continued utility is the monk epic.  Rogues, warriors, SK's, rangers, and paladins all bank their epics sooner or later.  It's pretty sad considering the work needed to obtain one and that it's supposed to be a truly nice item for those classes.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taldaydarfv>Taldaydar FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/24/02 10:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior epic ..</span><hr size=1> All that might change however with the rumored epic2 quests.... does anyone know more about these?<br>
